  </style>

<!-- ============ HEADER (shared shell) ============ -->

<!-- ============ HERO ============ -->
<section class="hero">
  <Svg19 class="botan hero-botan-tl" aria-hidden="true" />
  <Svg20 class="botan hero-botan-br" aria-hidden="true" />
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <p class="eyebrow">Zuo Yue Zi Meal Plan</p>
    <h1>Vita Meal</h1>
    <p class="cn-title">元氣月子餐</p>
    <p class="hero-sub">Lighter. Balanced. Simpler.</p>
    <p class="lede">Two full <em>Zuo Yue Zi</em> meals a day, cooked the traditional way — for the mother whose mornings are already taken care of.</p>
    <p class="hero-price"><span class="from">30 days · lunch, dinner &amp; a dessert</span>{usd(products.local_vita_30d.price)}</p>
    <div class="hero-cta">
      <a href="#pricing" class="btn btn-primary">See what's included</a>
      <a href="#taste" class="btn btn-ghost">Try a taste first</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <!-- HERO BANNER IMAGE — replace with a wide, warm shot of a full Vita meal (lunch + dinner + dessert), ~1600×640 -->
  <div class="hero-banner reveal">
    <div class="img-slot">
      <!-- <img src="images/vita-hero.jpg" alt="A full Vita Meal spread — lunch, dinner, and a dessert"> -->
      <span class="slot-icon">❀</span>
      <span class="slot-label">Hero Image</span>
      <span class="slot-hint">Wide, warm shot of a full Vita day — lunch, dinner &amp; dessert · ~1600 × 640</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ OPENING ============ -->
<section class="opening">
  <div class="narrow reveal">
    <p>If you're looking at a lighter plan and quietly wondering whether it still counts as doing Zuo Yue Zi <em>properly</em> — it's a fair question, and worth answering plainly.</p>
    <p>Here's the honest answer. Vita isn't a smaller version of the tradition. Your lunch arrives complete: a soup, an entrée, warm vegetables, rice and grains. Your dinner arrives complete: the Taiwanese postpartum soup, a second nourishing soup, an entrée, vegetables, rice and grains. A dessert. The daily healing drink. Nothing thinned out, nothing skipped.</p>
    <p class="pull">What Vita sets aside is breakfast — the one meal that's often already handled at home.</p>
    <p>In many households, breakfast is the meal that's already arranged — the one someone at home tends to take care of. Lunch and dinner are a different matter: the long-simmered soups, the slow braises, the dishes that shift week by week with your recovery. Those are the meals worth handing to us. So when breakfast is covered at home, Vita puts everything into the two meals that need us most, and asks nothing for the one that's already in hand.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="floral-divider reveal">
  <span class="line"></span>
  <Svg21 aria-hidden="true" />
  <span class="line r"></span>
</div>

<!-- ============ DAILY ============ -->
<section class="daily" id="daily">
  <Svg22 class="botan daily-botan" aria-hidden="true" />
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">What Arrives Every Day</p>
      <h2>Two full meals, and something sweet</h2>
      <p>Every day of your plan, delivered fresh:</p>
    </div>
    <div class="daily-grid reveal">
      <div class="daily-cell">
        <!-- IMAGE — a warming lunch soup (~600×400) -->
        <div class="img-slot"><span class="slot-icon">❀</span><span class="slot-label">Dish Photo</span><span class="slot-hint">A warming lunch soup · ~600 × 400</span></div>
        <div class="cell-body">
          <div class="num"><span>一</span></div>
          <h3>A complete lunch</h3>
          <p>Fish soup or the day's lunch soup, an entrée, warm vegetables, and rice and grains — the full midday meal, balanced the traditional way.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="daily-cell">
        <!-- IMAGE — Taiwanese postpartum soup or sesame oil chicken (~600×400) -->
        <div class="img-slot"><span class="slot-icon">❀</span><span class="slot-label">Dish Photo</span><span class="slot-hint">Taiwanese postpartum soup or a braise · ~600 × 400</span></div>
        <div class="cell-body">
          <div class="num"><span>二</span></div>
          <h3>A complete dinner</h3>
          <p>The Taiwanese postpartum soup, a second nourishing soup, an entrée, warm vegetables, and rice and grains — slow-simmered, never shortcut.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="daily-cell">
        <!-- IMAGE — a warm dessert (red bean soup, sweet soup) (~600×400) -->
        <div class="img-slot"><span class="slot-icon">❀</span><span class="slot-label">Dish Photo</span><span class="slot-hint">A warm dessert · ~600 × 400</span></div>
        <div class="cell-body">
          <div class="num"><span>三</span></div>
          <h3>A dessert &amp; your healing drink</h3>
          <p>One gentle dessert to close the day, and the daily healing drink that comes with every plan — because recovery can still be sweet.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ GALLERY ============ -->
<section class="gallery" id="gallery">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">On the Table</p>
      <h2>A look at the food</h2>
      <p>Real dishes from a Vita week.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="gallery-grid reveal">
      <!-- IMAGE — hero dish, tall (~800×880) -->
      <div class="img-slot"><span class="slot-icon">❀</span><span class="slot-label">Feature Dish</span><span class="slot-hint">Tall hero dish · ~800 × 880</span></div>
      <!-- IMAGE — square (~520×440) -->
      <div class="img-slot"><span class="slot-icon">❀</span><span class="slot-label">Dish</span><span class="slot-hint">~520 × 440</span></div>
      <!-- IMAGE — square (~520×440) -->
      <div class="img-slot"><span class="slot-icon">❀</span><span class="slot-label">Dish</span><span class="slot-hint">~520 × 440</span></div>
      <!-- IMAGE — square (~520×440) -->
      <div class="img-slot"><span class="slot-icon">❀</span><span class="slot-label">Dish</span><span class="slot-hint">~520 × 440</span></div>
      <!-- IMAGE — square (~520×440) -->
      <div class="img-slot"><span class="slot-icon">❀</span><span class="slot-label">Dish</span><span class="slot-hint">~520 × 440</span></div>
    </div>
    <p class="gallery-note">Menus rotate across the plan to follow the recovery sequence.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="floral-divider reveal">
  <span class="line"></span>
  <Svg21 aria-hidden="true" />
  <span class="line r"></span>
</div>

<!-- ============ PERSONA ============ -->
<section class="persona">
  <Svg23 class="botan persona-botan" aria-hidden="true" />
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="persona-grid reveal">
      <div class="persona-left">
        <p class="eyebrow">Perfect For You If…</p>
        <h2>Your mornings are already handled.</h2>
        <p>The Vita Meal is for the mom who wants lunch and dinner taken care of completely — and doesn't need breakfast on top.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="persona-right">
        <p>Maybe your mother or your partner is already up early, and breakfast is the one meal your household has arranged. When it's already in hand at home, there's no reason to have it delivered on top.</p>
        <p>So Vita covers the two meals that are hardest to manage yourself and leaves the one that's already handled to your household — a lighter plan, and a lighter cost, without cutting a single thing from your lunch or dinner.</p>
        <p>If your mornings <em>aren't</em> covered, though — if you'd rather wake to a warm meal already there and not think about food at all — that's exactly what the Classic plan is for, and it's worth every bit of it. Vita is simply for the mother who has breakfast handled.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ QUOTE ============ -->
<section class="quote-band">
  <div class="stamp-wm" style="top:50%;left:50%;transform:translate(-50%,-50%)"></div>
  <div class="quote-mark">"</div>
  <div class="quote-inner reveal">
    <p class="eyebrow">Moms Say</p>
    <p class="q">"I don't eat much in the mornings, so this was perfect — two proper meals a day, and nothing wasted."</p>
    <p class="by">— A Vita Meal mom</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ ADD-ONS ============ -->
<section class="addons" id="addons">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Make It Yours</p>
      <h2>Two ways to go deeper</h2>
      <p>The Vita plan is complete on its own. These add-ons are here if you want more.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="addon-grid reveal">
      <div class="addon-card">
        <!-- IMAGE — a cup of chicken essence (~760×400) -->
        <div class="img-slot"><span class="slot-icon">❀</span><span class="slot-label">Add-on Photo</span><span class="slot-hint">A cup of chicken essence · ~760 × 400</span></div>
        <div class="addon-body">
          <p class="tag">Recovery Booster</p>
          <h3>Slow-Simmered Chicken Essence</h3>
          <p class="cn">熬雞精</p>
          <p>Your go-to recovery booster — slowly simmered for hours from <strong>aged hens and white-feather chickens</strong> until every drop is rich with collagen, protein, and minerals, then concentrated into one small, warming cup.</p>
          <p>Easy to sip on the mornings you'd rather not eat a meal, it arrives ready to warm — no cooking, no cleanup. Mothers who add it tend to keep it for the whole month.</p>
          <p class="addon-price">{usd(products.chicken_essence.price)} / serving · add on whenever you like</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="addon-card">
        <!-- IMAGE — herbal drinks / packets (~760×400) -->
        <div class="img-slot"><span class="slot-icon">❀</span><span class="slot-label">Add-on Photo</span><span class="slot-hint">The daily herbal drinks · ~760 × 400</span></div>
        <div class="addon-body">
          <p class="tag">Herbal Add-On</p>
          <h3>The 30-Day Herbal Drinks</h3>
          <p class="cn">月子藥膳</p>
          <p>The daily herbal drinks that have anchored Chinese postpartum recovery for generations — <strong>15 formulas</strong> that follow the traditional recovery sequence, stage by stage across your thirty days.</p>
          <p>Because the formulas are staged week by week, most mothers start them on <strong>day one</strong>, alongside their first meals, so the sequence stays whole from the beginning.</p>
          <p class="addon-price">{usd(products.herbal_drink.price)} / day · one cup a day</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="floral-divider reveal">
  <span class="line"></span>
  <Svg21 aria-hidden="true" />
  <span class="line r"></span>
</div>

<!-- ============ PRICING ============ -->
<section class="pricing" id="pricing">
  <Svg24 class="botan pricing-botan" aria-hidden="true" />
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Choose Your Length</p>
      <h2>One plan, your timeline</h2>
      <p>Two full meals a day plus a dessert, delivered fresh daily. Pick the length that fits your recovery.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="price-grid reveal">
      <div class="price-card">
        <p class="mode">Every Day Includes</p>
        <h3>Vita Meal</h3>
        <p class="cn">元氣月子餐</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Lunch</strong> — fish soup or lunch soup, entrée, vegetables, rice &amp; grains</li>
          <li><strong>Dinner</strong> — Taiwanese postpartum soup, dinner soup, entrée, vegetables, rice &amp; grains</li>
          <li><strong>1 dessert</strong> + a daily healing drink</li>
          <li><strong>No breakfast</strong> — the one thing Vita leaves out</li>
          <li>Warm, cooked-from-scratch Zuo Yue Zi dishes, delivered fresh daily</li>
        </ul>
        <a href={orderUrl('local_vita', locale)} class="btn btn-primary">Order online</a>
      </div>
      <div class="price-card">
        <p class="mode">Pricing</p>
        <h3>By Length</h3>
        <p class="cn">依天數計費</p>
        <div class="tier-row feat"><span class="d">30 Days</span><span class="p">{usd(products.local_vita_30d.price)}</span></div>
        <div class="tier-row"><span class="d">21 Days</span><span class="p">{usd(products.local_vita_21d.price)}</span></div>
        <div class="tier-row"><span class="d">14 Days</span><span class="p">{usd(products.local_vita_14d.price)}</span></div>
        <div class="tier-row"><span class="d">1 Day</span><span class="p">{usd(products.local_vita_1d.price)}</span></div>
        <p class="dep">14–30 day plans: {usd(deposits.standard)} deposit · balance within 3 days of first delivery. 1-day: paid in full.</p>
        <a href={orderUrl('local_vita', locale)} class="btn btn-ghost">Order online</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="price-note reveal">Want the herbal drinks too? Add them for <strong>{usd(products.herbal_drink.price)} / day</strong> — one cup a day, add as many days as you like. Chicken essence can be added at <strong>{usd(products.chicken_essence.price)} / serving</strong>. Meals are delivered <strong>daily</strong>; remote areas receive every-other-day delivery and an additional delivery fee may apply.</p>
    <p class="pricing-foot">Not sure which length fits? Call us at <a href={`tel:${phones.main}`}>{phoneDisplay(phones.main)}</a> — we're happy to talk it through, no pressure.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ DOWNLOADS (shared block — reuse on every product page) ============ -->
<section class="actions" id="resources">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Review At Your Own Pace</p>
      <h2>Download the details</h2>
      <p>Prefer to look things over on your own? Grab the order form, compare every plan side by side, or browse the full menu.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="action-downloads reveal">
      <a href="https://file.jingmommy.com/f/Main_Order_Form.pdf" class="action-btn">
        <Svg25 class="ico" />
        <span class="lbl"><span class="en">Order Form <span class="pdf-tag">PDF</span></span><span class="cn">下載訂購單</span></span>
      </a>
      <a href="https://file.jingmommy.com/f/Meal_Comparison_Chart.pdf" class="action-btn">
        <Svg26 class="ico" />
        <span class="lbl"><span class="en">Meal Comparison Chart <span class="pdf-tag">PDF</span></span><span class="cn">餐點對照表</span></span>
      </a>
      <a href="https://file.jingmommy.com/f/Menu.pdf" class="action-btn">
        <Svg27 class="ico" />
        <span class="lbl"><span class="en">Full Menu <span class="pdf-tag">PDF</span></span><span class="cn">菜單</span></span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ UPGRADE ============ -->
<section class="upgrade">
  <div class="upgrade-inner reveal">
    <p class="eyebrow">Mornings Not Covered?</p>
    <h2>Then Classic is the one for you</h2>
    <p>If no one's handling breakfast at home, you shouldn't have to either. The Classic plan adds egg and porridge each morning and a second dessert — the full three-meal rhythm, so you wake to warm food already there and never think about a meal all month.</p>
    <a href={route("/plans", locale)} class="btn btn-primary">Explore the Classic Meal — {usd(products.local_classic_30d.price)}</a>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ FAQ ============ -->
<section class="faq-band" id="faq">
  <Svg28 class="botan faq-botan" aria-hidden="true" />
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Good Questions</p>
      <h2>Before you decide</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list reveal">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What's the difference between Vita and Classic?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Same kitchen, same recipes, same daily delivery. The Classic plan adds <em>breakfast</em> — egg and porridge — and a second dessert. Vita gives you the full lunch and the full dinner, plus one dessert and the daily healing drink. The simplest way to choose: if breakfast is already covered at home, Vita fits nicely; if it isn't, Classic is the one worth having.</p></div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Are two meals a day enough while I'm recovering?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Each Vita meal is a full recovery meal, not a smaller portion of one — lunch and dinner both arrive complete, with soup, an entrée, vegetables, and rice and grains. What Vita leaves out is breakfast. For mothers whose mornings are already covered at home, or who simply don't eat first thing, that's the natural fit. If you'd like breakfast handled too, the <a href={route("/plans", locale)}>Classic plan</a> is the better choice — and if you start with Vita and change your mind, call us and we'll sort it out.</p></div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Can I add the herbal drinks to the Vita plan?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes — the herbal drinks are an option on Vita at <strong>{usd(products.herbal_drink.price)} / day</strong>, one cup a day, for as many days as you like. The 15 formulas are staged to follow the traditional recovery sequence, so most mothers start them on day one, alongside their meals, and keep the full arc intact from the beginning.</p></div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How does delivery work?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>In our regular service area, meals are delivered fresh every day and we aim to reach your door before noon — though actual times can shift with traffic and routes, so an exact hour isn't guaranteed. Remote areas receive every-other-day delivery, delivery times there can't be guaranteed, and an additional delivery fee may apply. Refrigerate your meals when they arrive, and heat them thoroughly before eating.</p></div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>When should I order?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>At least one month before your due date, if you can. The week your baby arrives, you will not have the bandwidth to compare plans or fill out forms — and you shouldn't have to. Your start date can be adjusted once the baby comes.</p></div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ TASTE CTA ============ -->
<section class="taste" id="taste">
  <Svg29 class="botan taste-botan-l" aria-hidden="true" />
  <Svg30 class="botan taste-botan-r" aria-hidden="true" />
  <div class="taste-inner reveal">
    <p class="eyebrow">Not Sure Yet?</p>
    <h2>Taste before you commit.</h2>
    <p>Most mothers who choose the Vita plan tried a sample first. Have a day of meals delivered — and let the food make the case.</p>
    <div class="taste-cta">
      <a href={route("/sample", locale)} class="btn btn-primary">Order a sample day</a>
      <a href={route("/contact", locale)} class="btn btn-ghost">Contact us</a>
    </div>
    <p class="taste-note">Or call {phoneDisplay(phones.main)} — we're usually around later than you'd expect.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ FOOTER (shared shell) ============ -->

<script is:inline>
(function(){
  var els=document.querySelectorAll('.reveal');
  if(!('IntersectionObserver' in window)){els.forEach(function(e){e.classList.add('in')});return;}
  var io=new IntersectionObserver(function(entries){
    entries.forEach(function(en){
      if(en.isIntersecting){en.target.classList.add('in');io.unobserve(en.target);}
    });
  },{threshold:0.12,rootMargin:'0px 0px -40px 0px'});
  els.forEach(function(e){io.observe(e);});
  document.querySelectorAll('#nav a').forEach(function(a){
    a.addEventListener('click',function(){document.getElementById('nav').classList.remove('open');});
  });
})();
</script>
</Page>
